title: fix: Fix inlined templates in templates
body:
When a template is inline inside a WorkflowTemplate or ClusterWorkflowTemplate we must still create a stored version of it. This fix changes the 'name' given to those from `/scope/templateName/` (where after the last / should be a name but there isn't) to /scope/templateName/inline/name' where name can be step name or task name.

I have added inline as it's possible to name an inline step the same as a template in the same WorkflowTemplate.

Tested against the test cases from #10737.

Fixes #10737

title: chore: Remove legacy recursion preventer from template resolution
body:
The workflow template resolver used to be able to recurse. This was removed 2 years ago, but the code that prevents infinite recursion is still in the code base.
I have just removed code, and things still compile and tests pass. As I've changed a call interface and things still compile I'm happy I cannot have missed anything.
The UI has not changed

title: feat: Add operation configuration to gauge metric. Fixes #10662
body:
Hey, 
first time contributing to Argo, I've read the contributing guidelines but let me know if something else is needed.
 
Prometheus Gauge interface allows to Set(), Add() and Sub() to the metric's current value. However, Argo workflows only accept setting a new value. This PR implements a new configuration field to the gauge metric called `operation`. This field accepts three values: `Add`, `Set`, and `Sub`. To avoid breaking changes, it uses `Set` by default if the field is not configured.

Let me know what you think about the implementation. I can also add the field to the documentation examples.

Fixes #10662

  • add maxDepth option

  • Bring back the root option, albeit with slightly different semantics than in v8 and before.

High-Level Feature and API Surface Changes

  • Only support node 16 and higher.
  • Promise API instead of callbacks.
  • Exported function names have changed, as have the methods on the Glob class. See API documentation for details.
  • Accept pattern as string or array of strings.
  • Hybrid module distribution.
  • Full TypeScript support.
  • Exported Glob class is no longer an event emitter.
  • Exported Glob class has walk(), walkSync(), stream(), streamSync(), iterate(), iterateSync() methods, and is both an async and sync Generator.
  • First class support for UNC paths and drive letters on Windows. Note that glob patterns must still use / as a path separator, unless the windowsPathsNoEscape option is set, in which case glob patterns cannot be escaped with \.

title: fix: get configmap data when updating controller config Fixes #10659
body:
https://github.com/argoproj/argo-workflows/issues/10659 has details of the bug.

Verification steps:

0. I checkout master
1. `kind create cluster --name reproduction`
2. Install argo workflows w/ helm `helm install argo-workflows argo/argo-workflows --set controller.workflowDefaults.metadata.labels.simple=1 --version 0.22.13` (the 0.22.13 chart is using Argo Workflows v3.4.5)
3. I deploy a workflow. I see that it does set the label value.
4. I upgrade the default `helm install argo-workflows argo/argo-workflows --set controller.workflowDefaults.metadata.labels.simple=2 --version 0.22.13`
5. I verify in the configmap that the value has changed.
6. I deploy a workflow. It sets the label to the original value (simple: 1), not the new value.
7. When I look at the logs for the argo-workflows-controller, I see it knows there is an update, but I see it prints out the old version of the configmap
8. I checkout my branch.
9. I run `make workflow-controller-image`
10. I retag the image `docker tag quay.io/argoproj/workflow-controller:latest quay.io/argoproj/workflow-controller:me`
11. I load the image into kind `kind load docker-image quay.io/argoproj/workflow-controller:me --name reproduction`
12. I deploy the image `helm upgrade argo-workflows argo/argo-workflows --set controller.workflowDefaults.metadata.labels.simple=2 --set controller.image.tag=me --version 0.22.13 --set images.pullPolicy=IfNotPresent`
13. I deploy a workflow. See that it does set the label simple to 2.
14. I update the the workflowDefaults, `helm upgrade argo-workflows argo/argo-workflows --set controller.workflowDefaults.metadata.labels.simple=3 --set controller.image.tag=me --version 0.22.13 --set images.pullPolicy=IfNotPresent`
15. I deploy a workflow. See that it does set the label simple to 3.

Fixes #10659

In terms of implementation, I could have done this in other ways. I picked this approach because it is the least code added and therefore the simplest.
